text: <@U02688JHZ> do we know if/when google's planning on sending us all the background images for the skrillex campaign?
<@U02613K0X>: I didn't hear back on timing for photos - how much time will it take to get those set up in the database? If they send on Monday, can we still have all our work done EOD Monday?
For the front-end CMS updates, they'd prefer to have the date rather than "today" or "tomorrow" - otherwise, everything looks good. <@U02HAJ6JF>
Please let me know if there are any questions!
If we get all the files with something (semantic filename would be awesome) indicating their order, shouldn't take more than an hour to get them all uploaded and pulling.

And regarding the note about the frontend, <@U02HAJ6JF>, your life should be made easier by a property called "dateDisplayed" on today's images. You can just grab it (add a day to it for the set of editable images) instead of doing any date calculations.
Thats awesome. Thanks Jenny! I'll take a look.
